            PYTHON PROGRAMMING
              CHAPTER 1 OUTLINE
====================================================

Chapter Name:
Introduction to Python Programming

Topics Covered:

1. Introduction to Python
   • What is Python?
   • Features of Python
   • Applications of Python

2. Print Statement
   • print() function
   • Printing text
   • Printing numbers
   • Printing variables
   • Printing multiple values
   • Using sep parameter
   • Using end parameter

3. Escape Characters
   • \n  - New Line
   • \t  - Tab Space
   • \\  - Backslash
   • \"  - Double Quotes
   • \'  - Single Quote
   • \v  - Vertical Tab

4. Variables
   • What is a Variable?
   • Variable Declaration
   • Variable Initialization
   • Storing Values
   • Printing Variables

5. Data Types (Basic Introduction)
   • Integer (int)
   • Float (float)
   • String (str)
   • Boolean (bool)

6. Operators

   A. Arithmetic Operators
      • Addition (+)
      • Subtraction (-)
      • Multiplication (*)
      • Division (/)
      • Modulus (%)
      • Floor Division (//)
      • Exponent (**)

   B. Assignment Operators
      • =
      • +=
      • -=
      • *=
      • /=
      • %=
      • //=
      • **=

   C. Comparison (Relational) Operators
      • ==
      • !=
      • >
      • <
      • >=
      • <=

   D. Logical Operators
      • and
      • or
      • not

----------------------------------------------------
Learning Outcomes

After completing this chapter, students will be able to:

✓ Understand Python basics.
✓ Write and execute simple Python programs.
✓ Use the print() function effectively.
✓ Use escape characters in strings.
✓ Create and use variables.
✓ Identify basic data types.
✓ Perform arithmetic operations.
✓ Use assignment operators.
✓ Compare values using comparison operators.
✓ Apply logical operators in expressions.

